
[1]excitement

   EXCI'TEMENT, n. The act of exciting; stimulation.

   1. The state of being roused into action, or of having increased
   action. Stimulants are intended to produce excitement in the animal
   system.

   2. Agitation; a state of being roused into action; as an excitement of
   the people.

   3. That which excites or rouses; that which moves, stirs, or induces
   action; a motive.
